    <div xml:id="PN254">
      <lg type="edition">
<l>iḷaiyaru mutiyarum vēṟupulam paṭara</l>
<l>veṭuppa veḻāay mārpamaṇ pulla</l>
<l>viṭaiccurat tiṟutta maḷḷa viḷartta</l>
<l>vaḷaiyil vaṟuṅkai yōccik kiḷaiyu</l>
<l>ḷiṉṉa ṉāyiṉa ṉiḷaiyō ṉeṉṟu</l>
<l>niṉṉurai cellu māyiṉ maṟṟu</l>
<l>muṉṉūrp paḻuṉiya kōḷi yālattup</l>
<l>puḷḷār yāṇart taṟṟē yeṉmakaṉ</l>
<l>vaḷaṉuñ cemmalu memakkeṉa nāḷu</l>
<l>māṉātu pukaḻu maṉṉai</l>
<l>yāṅkā kuvaḷko laḷiyaḷ ṭāṉē.</l>
</lg>
<lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>You who won’t rise when roused, (2ab)</l>
<l>while young and old set out for another region, (1)</l>
<l>  while [your] chest embraces the earth, (2cd)</l>
<l>o warrior who tarries in the middle of the desert, (3a-c)</l>
<l>saying “the young man became like this” (5)</l>
<l>among [his] kin, wielding empty hand without bangles that became bare, (3d-4)</l>
<l>if you [thus] say your word (6)</l>
<l>the front village will be thus: of a fertility on which </l>
<l>birds become full, in the banyan tree. (7-8c)</l>
<l>The mother who praises [him] unendingly, (10)</l>
<l>saying “my son is for us prosperity and excellence”, (8d-9)</l>
<l>what will become of her? Pitiable she is. (11)  </l>
</lg>
    </div>
